title: PPPP’s Syed Sarfraz Hussain Shah wins PS- 32 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan People’s Party Parliamentarians’ (PPPP) Syed Sarfraz Hussain Shah has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-32 , Naushahro Feroze -I ,by securing 58,761 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Syed Zohaib Ali Shah of Grand Democratic Alliance, who bagged votes 27,413.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 44.95 %.
